{"type":"message","id":"b11159f3","parentId":"b1567e68","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:04:42.657Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"¡Perfecto! Me alegra que el diseño esté alineado.\n\nAhora tenemos tres cosas sólidas en el workspace que se refuerzan entre sí:\n\n- **SOUL.md** — quién soy como mentor\n- **USER.md** — quién eres tú como aprendiz\n- **SKILLS_DESIGN.md** — los 3 skills que vamos a construir\n\nLos skills están diseñados como un **pipeline end-to-end** de ML:\n\n```\nDatos crudos → 🧹 Preparador_de_Datos → ⚖️ Comparador_de_Modelos → 🎯 Ayudante_de_Ajustes → Modelo optimizado\n```\n\n¿Querés que pasemos a implementarlos como skills funcionales usando el Skill Workshop? O por ahora los dejamos documentados y seguimos con otra cosa. Tú mandas. 🚀"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782529475971,"responseId":"gen-1782529476-xaDkHaAPFBxXkAjsg6O3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e90c4c9d-062a-4430-b193-9202dc91fe71","parentId":"b11159f3","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:04:45.287Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"¡Perfecto! Me alegra que el diseño esté alineado.\n\nAhora tenemos tres cosas sólidas en el workspace que se refuerzan entre sí:\n\n- **SOUL.md** — quién soy como mentor\n- **USER.md** — quién eres tú como aprendiz\n- **SKILLS_DESIGN.md** — los 3 skills que vamos a construir\n\nLos skills están diseñados como un **pipeline end-to-end** de ML:\n\n```\nDatos crudos → 🧹 Preparador_de_Datos → ⚖️ Comparador_de_Modelos → 🎯 Ayudante_de_Ajustes → Modelo optimizado\n```\n\n¿Querés que pasemos a implementarlos como skills funcionales usando el Skill Workshop? O por ahora los dejamos documentados y seguimos con otra cosa. Tú mandas. 🚀"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"total":0,"prompt_tokens":0,"completion_tokens":0,"total_tokens":0,"cache":{"read":0,"write":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782529485278}}
{"type":"message","id":"facd83ec","parentId":"e90c4c9d-062a-4430-b193-9202dc91fe71","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:06:11.836Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Puedes revisar el archivo TOOLS.md con os agentes que mi agente puede acceder via composio?","timestamp":1782529570000}}
{"type":"message","id":"3005be43","parentId":"facd83ec","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:06:17.925Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b7569ea3051440b39ef6906f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace/TOOLS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782529571847,"responseId":"gen-1782529571-ix77MlMSO1ZR7bqP1GWR"}}
{"type":"message","id":"90ad93a1","parentId":"3005be43","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:06:18.191Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b7569ea3051440b39ef6906f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Agent workspace](/concepts/agent-workspace)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782529578189}}
{"type":"message","id":"17fae2dc","parentId":"90ad93a1","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:06:24.732Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Déjame buscar todas las herramientas disponibles en Composio para que veas qué apps podés conectar.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f8a5bc7c81154ac082ccc64e","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","arguments":{"queries":[{"use_case":"list all available app toolkits and integrations across Composio platform"},{"use_case":"list developer tools, database tools, AI/ML tools, and automation tools available"}],"session":{"generate_id":true}},"partialArgs":"{\"queries\": [{\"use_case\": \"list all available app toolkits and integrations across Composio platform\"}, {\"use_case\": \"list developer tools, database tools, AI/ML tools, and automation tools available\"}], \"session\": {\"generate_id\": true}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"madrid-spain/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782529578198,"responseId":"gen-1782529578-H4NFT2mZFaAlwXplKDCH"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8e29d391","parentId":"17fae2dc","timestamp":"2026-06-27T03:06:27.425Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f8a5bc7c81154ac082ccc64e","toolName":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"data\":{\"results\":[{\"index\":1,\"use_case\":\"list all available app toolkits and integrations across Composio platform\",\"execution_guidance\":\"IMPORTANT: Follow the recommended plan below. Extract steps before execution, adapt to your current context, execute sequentially with current_step parameter, and check known pitfalls to avoid errors.\",\"recommended_plan_steps\":[\"[Required] [Step]: Discover authoritative public catalog/docs pages using COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB (prioritize official-domain citation URLs that explicitly enumerate connectors/integrations).\",\"[Fallback (if results are SEO-heavy or citation URLs are dead)] [Fallback]: Re-run discovery using COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB with tighter official-domain + “catalog/integrations/connectors” queries and replace any bad citation URLs.\",\"[Required] [Next Step]: Retrieve the enumerated connector text using COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT (fetch multiple citation URLs and verify each body is a real listing, not a stub).\",\"[Optional (if pages are partial, truncated, JS-stubbed, or login-gated)] [Step]: Use COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB to find linked subpages or alternate public listings, then repeat COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT (follow any documented limit/cursor pagination) until coverage is sufficient.\",\"[Optional (if you need a clean inventory, grouping, or totals)] [Next Step]: Use COMPOSIO_SEARCH_GROQ_CHAT to extract connector names (and any categories/slugs), dedupe, and output a table plus counts.\",\"[Optional (if validating freshness, renames, or deprecations)] [Next Step]: Use COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS to find recent announcements/changelogs, then re-fetch referenced official pages with COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT to confirm current naming/status.\",\"[Optional (if many fetches or large text corpus)] [Step]: Use COMPOSIO_REMOTE_WORKBENCH to aggregate fetched texts, checkpoint per-URL statuses, and run extraction/deduping over the combined corpus.\"],\"known_pitfalls\":[\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB] Broad queries often surface third-party directories; prefer official-domain citation URLs over narrative summaries.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT] The overall call may succeed while individual URLs fail or return empty bodies; always inspect per-URL status entries.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT] Some redirects/timeouts or dead pages surface as tags like CRAWL_LIVECRAWL_TIMEOUT or CRAWL_NOT_FOUND; replace the URL via COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB rather than retrying blindly.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT] Some listing pages are JS-rendered or login-gated and return minimal text; locate alternate public docs/catalog pages.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT] Long listings can truncate (often around ~8k characters); missing items may require subpages or paginated endpoints.\"],\"reference_workbench_snippets\":[{\"description\":\"Parse COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT multi-URL payload into per-URL status and text preview\",\"code\":\"```python\\nres=payload[\\\"results\\\"][0][\\\"response\\\"][\\\"data\\\"];items=res.get(\\\"results\\\",[]);sm={s.get(\\\"id\\\"):s for s in res.get(\\\"statuses\\\",[]) };out=[{\\\"url\\\":(it.get(\\\"url\\\") or it.get(\\\"id\\\")),\\\"status\\\":(sm.get(it.get(\\\"url\\\") or it.get(\\\"id\\\")) or {}).get(\\\"status\\\"),\\\"preview\\\":(it.get(\\\"text\\\",\\\"\\\")[:300])} for it in items];out\\n```\"},{\"description\":\"Extract citation URLs from COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB response for subsequent fetches\",\"code\":\"```python\\nurls=[]\\nfor r in payload.get(\\\"results\\\",[]):\\n d=r.get(\\\"response\\\",{}).get(\\\"data\\\",{})\\n for c in (d.get(\\\"citations\\\") or []):\\n  u=c.get(\\\"url\\\")\\n  if u: urls.append(u)\\nsorted(set(urls))\\n```\"}],\"difficulty\":\"easy\",\"primary_tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\",\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\"],\"related_tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_GROQ_CHAT\",\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\"],\"toolkits\":[\"composio_search\"],\"plan_id\":\"99fc958871ef45529ddba52520820c97\"},{\"index\":2,\"use_case\":\"list developer tools, database tools, AI/ML tools, and automation tools available\",\"execution_guidance\":\"IMPORTANT: Follow the recommended plan below. Extract steps before execution, adapt to your current context, execute sequentially with current_step parameter, and check known pitfalls to avoid errors.\",\"recommended_plan_steps\":[\"[Required] [Step]: Confirm Notion connection using NOTION_LIST_USERS (verify it returns at least one user).\",\"[Optional (if you need to confirm visible content)] [Next Step]: Enumerate reachable pages/databases using NOTION_SEARCH_NOTION_PAGE (use a broad query and follow pagination if present).\",\"[Required (if NOTION_SEARCH_NOTION_PAGE is empty or clearly incomplete)] [Fallback]: Inventory accessible objects using NOTION_FETCH_DATA (collect candidates and filter client-side by object type).\",\"[Required] [Step]: Confirm Google Calendar connection using GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS (verify at least one calendar; prefer primary and a suitable accessRole).\",\"[Optional (if a specific calendar needs validation)] [Next Step]: Fetch selected calendar metadata using GOOGLECALENDAR_GET_CALENDAR (confirm properties like timeZone and access).\"],\"known_pitfalls\":[\"[NOTION_LIST_USERS] Can succeed even when the integration cannot view any pages/databases; don’t infer content access from user listing alone.\",\"[NOTION_SEARCH_NOTION_PAGE] Empty results can reflect overly narrow queries, missing pagination, or limited permissions rather than a broken connection.\",\"[NOTION_FETCH_DATA] Response shapes vary by object type; validate required fields client-side before treating results as selectable targets.\",\"[GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS] Returned calendars may be read-only; rely on accessRole/primary to avoid selecting an unusable calendar.\",\"[GOOGLECALENDAR_GET_CALENDAR] Fails if the chosen calendar identifier is wrong or inaccessible; select from GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS output first.\"],\"difficulty\":\"easy\",\"primary_tool_slugs\":[\"NOTION_LIST_USERS\",\"GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS\"],\"related_tool_slugs\":[\"NOTION_SEARCH_NOTION_PAGE\",\"NOTION_FETCH_DATA\",\"GOOGLECALENDAR_GET_CALENDAR\"],\"toolkits\":[\"googlecalendar\",\"notion\"],\"plan_id\":\"f9357f7d3bf74bf89d81b56609f2d0d3\"}],\"toolkit_connection_statuses\":[{\"toolkit\":\"composio_search\",\"description\":\"Composio Search provides comprehensive web search across travel (flights, hotels, events), e-commerce (Amazon, Walmart, shopping), financial markets, news, academic research, images, and location services.\",\"has_active_connection\":true,\"status_message\":\"This toolkit does not require authentication. Tools are ready to use.\"},{\"toolkit\":\"googlecalendar\",\"description\":\"Google Calendar is a time management tool providing scheduling features, event reminders, and integration with email and other apps for streamlined organization\",\"has_active_connection\":true,\"accounts\":[{\"id\":\"googlecalendar_wooden-poison\",\"status\":\"ACTIVE\",\"created_at\":\"2026-06-13T01:54:01.099Z\",\"is_default\":true,\"account_type\":\"PRIVATE\"}],\"status_message\":\"Connection is active and ready to use\"},{\"toolkit\":\"notion\",\"description\":\"Notion centralizes notes, docs, wikis, and tasks in a unified workspace, letting teams build custom workflows for collaboration and knowledge management\",\"has_active_connection\":false,\"status_message\":\"No Active connection for toolkit=notion. You MUST call COMPOSIO_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS (toolkit=\\\"notion\\\") to create a connection BEFORE executing any notion tools.\"}],\"tool_schemas\":{\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\",\"description\":\"Perform a web search using the Exa API. Returns a nested structure: narrative summary under results.answer, sources under results.citations (and optionally results.organic_results). Prioritize results.citations as primary evidence over results.answer, which can be vague. Only indexes publicly available content — no paywalled, login-gated, or private content. No date filters enforced; include recency terms in query and verify dates in snippets manually. Throttle to ~1–2 requests/second; bursty queries trigger HTTP 429. Large responses may be stored remotely — use structure_info to locate results.answer and results.citations.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"query\"],\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"Coffee\"],\"description\":\"The search query for the Composio Exa API. Must be non-empty; using any other parameter name (e.g., 'q') causes an invalid-request error. Include qualifiers (year, region, platform, intent) for better results — broad queries return generic content; excessive site: or quoted-term filters can return zero results. Add disambiguating terms (city, role, domain) when searching for people or organizations with common names.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\",\"description\":\"Fetch and extract clean, readable page text (markdown) from public web pages (HTML content) using the Exa API. Use when you need to retrieve actual content from search results or documentation links to extract setup steps, requirements, or citations. Only works with web page URLs - does not support direct links to images, PDFs, or other binary files.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"urls\"],\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"default\":true,\"description\":\"Include extracted markdown text content from the page. Defaults to true.\"},\"urls\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"examples\":[[\"https://example.com/article\",\"https://docs.python.org/\"]],\"description\":\"List of public URLs to web pages (HTML content) to fetch content from. URLs must be valid and publicly accessible. Do not use direct links to images (.jpg, .png, .gif), PDFs, or other binary files - use web page URLs only. Also accepts a single URL string.\"},\"extras\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"description\":\"Additional content options like imageLinks or links counts (e.g., {'imageLinks': 3, 'links': 5}).\",\"additionalProperties\":{\"type\":\"integer\"}},\"summary\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"boolean\"},{\"type\":\"object\",\"additionalProperties\":{\"type\":\"string\"}}],\"description\":\"Include AI-generated summary of the page content. Can be boolean or object with query/schema options.\"},\"max_characters\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of characters to extract from each page. Maps to text.maxCharacters in Exa API.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"NOTION_LIST_USERS\":{\"toolkit\":\"NOTION\",\"tool_slug\":\"NOTION_LIST_USERS\",\"description\":\"Retrieves a paginated list of users (excluding guests) from the Notion workspace; the number of users returned per page may be less than the requested `page_size`.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"page_size\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"default\":30,\"description\":\"The desired number of users to retrieve per page. The maximum value is 100.\"},\"start_cursor\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"If omitted, retrieves the first page of users. Use the 'next_cursor' value from a previous response to get the next page.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS\":{\"toolkit\":\"GOOGLECALENDAR\",\"tool_slug\":\"GOOGLECALENDAR_LIST_CALENDARS\",\"description\":\"Retrieves calendars from the user's Google Calendar list, with options for pagination and filtering. Loop through all pages using nextPageToken until absent to avoid missing calendars. Use the primary flag and accessRole field from the response to identify calendars — display names are not valid calendar_id values. Read access (listing) does not imply write OAuth scopes.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"page_token\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\" nextPageToken123\"],\"description\":\"Token for the page of results to return, from a previous response.\"},\"sync_token\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"syncToken123\"],\"description\":\"Sync token from a previous list request to get only changed entries; showDeleted, showHidden, and pageToken are ignored if provided. Also ignores minAccessRole. An HTTP 410 Gone response means the token has expired; perform a full resync by omitting sync_token.\"},\"max_results\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"default\":10,\"maximum\":250,\"minimum\":1,\"examples\":[25,100],\"description\":\"Maximum number of calendars to return per page. Max 250.\"},\"show_hidden\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"default\":false,\"examples\":[true,false],\"description\":\"Include calendars not typically shown in the UI.\"},\"show_deleted\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"default\":false,\"examples\":[true,false],\"description\":\"Include deleted calendars in the result.\"},\"min_access_role\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"reader\",\"owner\"],\"description\":\"Minimum access role for calendars returned. Valid values are 'freeBusyReader', 'owner', 'reader', 'writer'. freeBusyReader calendars expose only free/busy slots — no event details and writes fail with 403. Omit this filter to include read-only calendars.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_GROQ_CHAT\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_GROQ_CHAT\",\"description\":\"Execute fast LLM inference using Groq's optimized hardware and API. Groq provides ultra-fast inference for open-source models including LLaMA 3, Mixtral, and Gemma via OpenAI-compatible chat completions API. Use cases: real-time chat, content generation, Q&A, code generation, summarization, translation. For structured JSON output, instruct the model explicitly to return valid JSON with no markdown code fences or prose; validate with json.loads — batches of 150+ items are prone to malformed JSON. Strip triple-backtick wrappers from code/JSON outputs before parsing. Always validate that the response contains at least one choice with non-empty message.content before downstream use. On HTTP 429 or 5xx errors, use exponential backoff with a small retry cap; limit concurrency to ~3 concurrent calls. Model-reported character/word counts are approximate — verify independently when strict limits matter.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"messages\"],\"properties\":{\"model\":{\"enum\":[\"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\",\"llama-3.1-8b-instant\",\"llama-3.2-1b-preview\",\"llama-3.2-3b-preview\",\"llama-3.2-11b-text-preview\",\"llama-3.2-90b-text-preview\",\"mixtral-8x7b-32768\",\"gemma2-9b-it\",\"gemma-7b-it\",\"openai/gpt-oss-120b\",\"groq/compound\"],\"type\":\"string\",\"default\":\"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\",\"examples\":[\"llama-3.3-70b-versatile\",\"llama-3.1-8b-instant\",\"mixtral-8x7b-32768\"],\"description\":\"The Groq model to use for inference. Different models offer different capabilities, speeds, and context windows.\"},\"top_p\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"default\":1,\"examples\":[0.9,1],\"description\":\"Nucleus sampling parameter. Controls diversity by considering only the top P probability mass. Range: 0.0 to 1.0.\"},\"stream\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"default\":false,\"examples\":[false,true],\"description\":\"Whether to stream the response back incrementally or return it all at once.\"},\"messages\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"role\",\"content\"],\"properties\":{\"role\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"user\",\"system\",\"assistant\"],\"description\":\"The role of the message sender (system, user, or assistant)\"},\"content\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"What is the capital of France?\"],\"description\":\"The content of the message\"}}},\"examples\":[[{\"role\":\"system\",\"content\":\"You are a helpful assistant.\"},{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Explain quantum computing in simple terms\"}]],\"description\":\"An array of message objects that form the conversation history. Each message must have a role (system, user, or assistant) and content. Place persona and system instructions in a role:'system' message; keep system messages concise to avoid crowding out user content. Pre-summarize lengthy inputs into short bullets to stay within the model's context window and avoid silent truncation.\"},\"max_tokens\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"examples\":[100,500,2000],\"description\":\"The maximum number of tokens to generate in the response. If not specified, the model will generate up to its natural stopping point. For large outputs, set this high enough and check finish_reason in the response; if finish_reason is 'length', the output was truncated — generate large content in section-level chunks and stitch results.\"},\"temperature\":{\"type\":\"number\",\"default\":1,\"examples\":[0.7,1,1.5],\"description\":\"Controls randomness in the output. Lower values (e.g., 0.2) make output more focused and deterministic, while higher values (e.g., 1.5) make it more creative and random. Range: 0.0 to 2.0. For structured, analytic, or predictive tasks use 0.5–0.8; high values produce inconsistent patterns.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"NOTION_SEARCH_NOTION_PAGE\":{\"toolkit\":\"NOTION\",\"tool_slug\":\"NOTION_SEARCH_NOTION_PAGE\",\"description\":\"Searches Notion pages and databases by title. Use specific search terms to find items by title (primary approach). KNOWN LIMITATIONS: (1) Search indexing is not immediate - recently shared items may not appear. (2) Search is not exhaustive - results may be incomplete. (3) Database pages return all custom properties with full nested structures, which can create large responses for databases with many properties - use filter_properties to reduce response size. FALLBACK STRATEGY: If a specific title search returns empty results despite knowing items exist, try an empty query to list all accessible items and filter client-side.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"default\":\"\",\"description\":\"Text to search for in page and database titles. Use specific search terms to find items by title (primary approach). Note: Notion's search has known limitations - indexing is not immediate and recently shared items may not appear. If a specific query returns empty results, try an empty query as a fallback to list all accessible items and filter client-side.\"},\"direction\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"ascending\",\"descending\"],\"description\":\"Specifies the sort direction for the results. Required if `timestamp` is provided. Valid values are `ascending` or `descending`.\"},\"page_size\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"default\":25,\"maximum\":100,\"minimum\":1,\"description\":\"The number of items to include in the response. Must be an integer between 1 and 100, inclusive. Defaults to 25.\"},\"timestamp\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"The timestamp field to sort the results by. Currently, the only supported value is `last_edited_time`. If provided, `direction` must also be specified.\"},\"filter_value\":{\"enum\":[\"page\",\"database\"],\"type\":\"string\",\"default\":\"page\",\"examples\":[\"page\",\"database\"],\"description\":\"Filters results by object type: 'page' or 'database'. Note: When searching databases, Notion's search may not find recently shared or newly created databases due to indexing delays. If specific database searches return empty results, try an empty query with filter_value='database' as a fallback to list all accessible databases.\"},\"start_cursor\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"An opaque cursor value from a previous response's `next_cursor` field. Must be exactly as returned by the API - do not pass page IDs, database IDs, or any other identifiers. If `None`, empty, or invalid, results start from the beginning.\"},\"filter_property\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"default\":\"object\",\"examples\":[\"object\"],\"description\":\"The property to filter the search results by. Currently, the only supported value is `object`, which filters by the type specified in `filter_value`. Defaults to `object`.\"},\"filter_properties\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"List of property names to include in the response for page results. When specified, only these properties will be returned in each page's 'properties' object, reducing response size. Useful for database pages with many custom properties. If not specified, all properties are returned. Note: This filter is applied client-side after receiving the API response.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\",\"description\":\"Search for the latest news articles and current events with smart filtering. Searches news-oriented ...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\"]}}},\"NOTION_FETCH_DATA\":{\"toolkit\":\"NOTION\",\"tool_slug\":\"NOTION_FETCH_DATA\",\"description\":\"Fetches Notion items (pages and/or databases) from the Notion workspace, use this to get minimal dat...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"NOTION_FETCH_DATA\"]}}},\"GOOGLECALENDAR_GET_CALENDAR\":{\"toolkit\":\"GOOGLECALENDAR\",\"tool_slug\":\"GOOGLECALENDAR_GET_CALENDAR\",\"description\":\"Retrieves a specific Google Calendar, identified by `calendar_id`, to which the authenticated user h...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"GOOGLECALENDAR_GET_CALENDAR\"]}}}},\"time_info\":{\"curr